item.description:
Since bspwm doesn&rsquo;t handle any keyboard input we need to use a third party program such as, sxhkd or polybar to switch between keyboard layouts.
First we need to create a script. Here is an example for a script that switch between English and Arabic:
#!/bin/bash  # Switching between keyboard layouts CURRENT_LAYOUT=$(setxkbmap -query | awk &#39;NR==3{print $2}&#39;) if [ &#34;$CURRENT_LAYOUT&#34; = &#34;us&#34; ]; then # To switch to arabic setxkbmap &#34;ar&#34; else setxkbmap &#34;us&#34; fi Then, make the script executable using chmod +x
